# TanStack Documentation

Use current TanStack docs — do not rely on training data for API details.

## Priority 1: TanStack MCP server

If the `tanstack` MCP server is available, use these tools:

1. `search_tanstack_docs` — find pages by keyword; filter with `library` (`start`, `router`, `query`, `form`, `devtools`, `cli`)
2. `fetch_tanstack_doc` — get full Markdown for a page path found via search
3. `list_tanstack_libraries` — discover libraries, versions, and docs URLs

Workflow: search first, then fetch the most relevant page.

## Priority 2: Context7 MCP (fallback)

If the TanStack MCP server is unavailable, use Context7 `resolve-library-id` then `query-docs`:

| Product | Preferred Context7 library ID |
| --- | --- |
| TanStack Start | `/websites/tanstack_start_framework_react` |
| TanStack Router | `/tanstack/router` |
| TanStack Query | `/tanstack/query` |
| TanStack Form | `/tanstack/form` |
| TanStack DevTools | `/tanstack/devtools` |
| TanStack CLI | `/tanstack/cli` |

Pass the user's full question as the `query` parameter.

## Priority 3: TanStack CLI (shell fallback)

```bash
# Search docs
npx @tanstack/cli search-docs "server functions" --library start --framework react --json

# Fetch a specific page
npx @tanstack/cli doc router "framework/react/overview" --json
npx @tanstack/cli doc query "framework/react/guides/queries" --json
npx @tanstack/cli doc form "framework/react/guides/basic-concepts" --json
npx @tanstack/cli doc devtools "overview" --json
npx @tanstack/cli doc cli "cli-reference" --json

# List all libraries
npx @tanstack/cli libraries --json
```

